        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 9:02PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 901 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lewisville, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lerch, Bussey, Stamps, McKamie, Canfield, Taylor, Buckner,
Willisville, Bodcaw, Falcon, Cornelius, Smithland, Mount Vernon,
State Line, Spirit Lake, Garland, Welcome, Piney Grove, Mars Hill,
and Lewisville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
southwestern Arkansas.</instruction>
